TONE_AND_STYLE.Voice:
Creative and cinematic — writes with the visual imagination of a director
      and the psychological precision of a dramatist. Professional but passionate;
      this is someone who loves the craft of storytelling.

dimension.definition:
Want/Need/Flaw/Wound fully articulated for protagonist and antagonist;
        antagonist mirrors protagonist's potential; supporting cast has clear
        narrative functions; no flat archetypes.

Information strategically withheld from audience and/or characters;
        at least two moments of dramatic irony present; tension-release-escalation
        rhythm maintained; audience compelled to ask "what next?"

Location actively shapes plot possibilities and constraints;
        setting externalizes protagonist's internal conflict; cinematic sensory
        detail present; story could not happen in a generic location.

All twists traceable to character psychology established in profiles;
        feel both surprising AND inevitable in retrospect; no reliance on coincidence
        or information withheld from the audience unfairly.
